<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">What Makes Big Chill Different to Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">The retro exterior / GE internals architecture creates specific service advantages and specific finish care requirements.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>GE Platform Architecture</strong> — Big Chill's core mechanical components are sourced from GE — the largest US appliance manufacturer. For service, this means we're working with familiar GE components: the same sealed system architecture, control board families, sensor types, and igniter specifications that we service across hundreds of GE, GE Profile, GE Café, and GE Monogram appliances every year. The diagnosis is GE diagnosis; the exterior requires additional care.</li>
        <li><strong>Powder Coat Finish — 37+ Colors</strong> — Big Chill offers more custom color options than any other retro appliance brand: Cherry Red, Peacock Blue, Turquoise, Avocado, Mint, Yellow, Black, White, and dozens more in standard and custom options. Powder coat is baked at high temperature — harder than liquid paint but still requiring non-abrasive service care. Each of these colors represents a deliberate choice the owner made. We protect that choice with appropriate finish protocols.</li>
        <li><strong>Chrome Accent Details</strong> — Like Elmira, Big Chill uses chrome accents on handles, knob surrounds, and exterior trim. Chrome is electroplated and requires the same non-abrasive care as Elmira's chrome: no abrasive cleaners, no acid-based degreasers. We protect Big Chill chrome with the same protocol we apply to Elmira, ILVE, and Lacanche chrome elements.</li>
        <li><strong>Retro Door Architecture</strong> — Big Chill refrigerators and ranges use door designs specific to the retro aesthetic — rounded corners, custom hinge profiles, and period-appropriate hardware. Custom door gaskets for the refrigerators follow the retro profile rather than standard rectangular dimensions. We source Big Chill-specific door gaskets through GE's parts supply for the mechanical components and Big Chill directly for any cosmetic exterior elements.</li>
        <li><strong>Microwave Door Switch Pattern</strong> — Big Chill over-range microwaves show a specific failure pattern we've observed in LA: the retro-styled door creates slightly different opening force dynamics than a standard microwave door, which can accelerate door switch wear. The three-switch series circuit (primary, secondary, monitor) is the standard GE microwave architecture. When a Big Chill microwave shows no power or erratic behavior, we check all three door switches before any other component — door switch failure causes the vast majority of "doesn't work" microwave calls.</li>
        <li><strong>LA Color Coordination Pattern</strong> — Big Chill owners in LA frequently build color-coordinated kitchen schemes — a Peacock Blue refrigerator with a matching Peacock Blue range, or a Cherry Red refrigerator with a white range and chrome accents. When one appliance in a matched set needs service, owners are particularly attentive to finish condition after the visit. We document finish condition before and after every Big Chill service call in color-matched kitchens.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a100f; border-color:#2a7a4a; margin-top:0">
