<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common Big Chill Failures in Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">❄️ Refrigerator Not Cooling</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">GE platform defrost system or start relay failure — the same diagnosis we apply to GE refrigerators broadly. Defrost heater, start relay, evaporator fan, or temperature sensor. LA summer heat in Silver Lake and Echo Park inland locations stresses condenser performance. We clean condenser coils on every Big Chill refrigerator cooling call as standard practice.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-fridge">Refrigerator</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Range Igniter Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">GE-platform ceramic igniter tip degradation — normal thermal cycling wear plus accelerated coastal salt air corrosion at coastal LA properties. Igniters are GE-spec components available through standard GE parts channels, typically same-day. We inspect all burner igniters on every Big Chill range call — slow ignition indicates degradation before complete failure.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-range">Range</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🎨 Powder Coat Damage from Service</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Previous technician used abrasive or acid-based cleaner on the powder coat finish — dull spots or etch marks are visible on the colored surface. Powder coat can be addressed with professional touch-up for small areas; significant damage requires professional respray to maintain color match. We protect Big Chill finish throughout every service call and never use abrasive or acid agents on powder coat.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-finish">Powder Coat</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">📟 Microwave Door Switch</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Three-switch door circuit failure — one of the series door switches has failed, causing the microwave to lose power or behave erratically. Door switch failure is the most common Big Chill microwave call by far — 10× more common than magnetron failure. We test all three door switches before any other component assessment. Same-day GE-spec door switches in most cases.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Microwave</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Oven Temperature Drift</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">GE-platform temperature sensor drift or thermostat calibration offset. We test with a calibrated probe at multiple setpoints before ordering parts — many Big Chill oven temperature complaints resolve with calibration adjustment without replacement. Same diagnostic approach as GE Café and GE Profile, which share the same platform architecture.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">💧 Dishwasher Not Draining</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">GE-platform pump or drain valve failure combined with LA hard water spray arm scale. We address scale simultaneously with drain component service — hard water at 250–400 ppm creates a compound blockage pattern that affects both drain performance and wash quality. Post-service descale frequency reset for LA water hardness.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Dishwasher</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

